raw_data.description: Responsible for managing all aspects of several complex programs simultaneously. Experienced in areas of performance measurement and Business Process Reengineering (BPR) methodologies. May conduct process modeling and analysis. Organizes, directs, and coordinates planning and production of all contract support activities. raw_data.title: Business Analyst
raw_data.description: Reviews, analyzes, and evaluates user needs to create systems solutions that support overall business and IT strategies. Applies both business and technical expertise through industry recognized methods in the delivery of work products.  Analyzes business/technical needs and processes for configuration or programming within applications, gathers and organizes data to configure standard reports, analyzes data to identify trends and patterns.  Develops diagrams and flowcharts, analyzes, and modifies systems to support an organization’s application systems.  Identifies required inputs and formats the output to meet user’s needs.  Assists in the preparation and conduct of business analyses and studies, needs assessments, requirements analysis/definition and cost/benefit analyses to align business systems, solutions, and initiatives. Prepares forecasts and analyzes trends and metrics, performance measurements, reports and recommendations. Documents system requirements, defines scope and objectives, and creates system specifications that drive system development and implementation. Provides knowledge and analysis of highly specialized applications and operational environments, high-level functional systems analysis, design, integration, documentation, and implementation advice.  Identifies causes for deviations, business and/or technical risks and recommends corrective action.
